The paper discusses the effective performance of information retrieval on the web, which falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also proposes the use of data structure concepts for implementation of scheduler and circular queue, which falls under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the parallelization policy, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the design of a software agent, which falls under the category of Software Engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the optimization of the web crawler, which falls under the category of Databases (cs.DB).
